  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pot over medium heat.",
    "Add minced ginger and garlic, sauté until fragrant.",
    "Pour in diced tomatoes and cook until they soften and release juices.",
    "Stir in kombu water, coconut milk, and fermented soybean paste.",
    "Add cumin, turmeric, salt, and brown sugar, stirring to combine.",
    "Simmer the soup for 10 minutes, allowing flavors to meld.",
    "Use an immersion blender to puree until silky smooth.",
    "Return to low heat, season with white pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro if desired.",
    "Serve hot with a side of steamed rice or hot buns."
